    • getHistoryObservationRetryMinus

      public int getHistoryObservationRetryMinus()
      Monitoring of historical price data. Transmission error with maximum repetition "gt.history.retry" minus this number. If "gt.history.retry" contains the value 4, this value should be 0 or 1. Thus, an instrument with 4 or 3 retries would be considered non-functioning.
      Returns:
      Value that is subtracted from the "gt.history.retry" value.

    • getHistoryObservationDaysBack

      public int getHistoryObservationDaysBack()
      Monitoring of historical price data. The instrument is only taken into account if a successful transfer has taken place within the current date minus this number of days. In this way, any instruments that are no longer active but are listed as active do not distort the calculation.
      Returns:
      Number of days

    • getHistoryObservationFallingPercentage

      public int getHistoryObservationFallingPercentage()
      Monitoring of historical price data. Message when at least this percentage of a connector has failed. At 100%, the connector probably no longer works at all.
      Returns:
      Percentage threshold
